Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden have departed for Egypt, Kenya, and South Africa. In Egypt, Biden will meet with President Mubarak to discuss bilateral and regional issues. In Kenya, he will meet with President Kibaki and Prime Minister Odinga to discuss bilateral issues and peace and stability in the region, particularly in Sudan and Somalia. Finally, in South Africa, Biden will meet with Deputy President Motlanthe, Foreign Minister Nkoana-Mashabane, and other world leaders attending the 2010 FIFA World Cup. He will represent the United States at the opening ceremonies and attend the U.S. Men’s National Team’s first game before returning to Washington, DC.